Different frequency scalings apply to mass quadrupole and mass current quadrupole emission. The most promising source of the mass current non-axisymmetry in neutron stars is thought to be “r\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
