				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\gamma $$\end{document}-ray observations valid over the gravitational-wave observation time. The precision must also be high in following up outliers from directed or all-sky searches, while much less precision is needed in the first stage of hierarchical searches. This section describes the intrinsic signal model assumed, along with the expected modulations due to detector motion.

