For a bin-centered signal and rectangular windowing, the filter would be a Kronecker delta, but in general, spectral leakage favors use of a handful of neighboring bins, to recover the full signal strength. By coherently combining the resulting extracted complex coefficients from the observed segments, one can achieve a full, coherent demodulation of the signal.10 Table 1 shows example power fractions in adjacent DFT bins (using rectangular windowing) for a monochromatic signal that is bin-centered or offset positively from the bin center by bin fractions of 0.1-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
